HEADWORD: Infusionism
<hw>In*fu"sion*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The doctrine
that the soul is preexistent to the body, and is infused into it at
conception or birth; -- opposed to <contr>traducianism</contr> and
<contr>creationism</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Infusive</ent>⟦br⟧
